HEADWORD: Donatist
<hw>Don"a*tist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>Donatista</ets>: cf. F. <ets>Donatiste</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Eccl.
Hist.)</fld> <def>A follower of Donatus, the leader of a body of North
African schismatics and purists, who greatly disturbed the church in the
4th century. They claimed to be the true church.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

